title: Two Telugu girls arrested for 'shoplifting' in US

description: The new 3XO will get XUV 400 EV-inspired dashboard layout and it’s expected to get a 10.25-inch floating touchscreen infotainment system with c wireless Apple CarPlay/Android Auto, AdrenoX connected car tech, cruise control, 10.25-inch fully digital instrument cluster, dual-zone climate control, rear AC vents, type-C USB outlets and more.
title: Mahindra XUV 3XO to get these first-in-segment features: Teased again

description: Google terminated 28 employees for protesting against a $1.2 billion contract with Israel. The company emphasized intolerance towards disruptive behavior, leading to the firings, despite protests from employee groups.
title: Google sacks 28 employees for protests over 'Israel contract'

description: Israel has vowed to respond to Iran’s unprecedented attack without saying when or how, leaving the region bracing for further escalation after months of unrest linked to the ongoing war in Gaza. Israel’s allies have been urging Israel since the attack to hold back on any response that could spiral. These calls were repeated on Wednesday during visits by the British and German foreign ministers.
title: 'Nowhere will be safe': How Iran is preparing for possible Israeli retaliation

description: Cricket world is eagerly awaiting India's T20 World Cup squad reveal, with Rishabh Pant's remarkable comeback sparking discussions about his potential selection in the final 15. Pant has amassed 194 runs in six matches, maintaining a strike rate of 157.72. Stuart Broad has been a vocal advocate for his inclusion.
title: 'He's ready': Eng great backs this India star for T20 WC selection

description: Delhi airport saw ten flights to Dubai and nine incoming flights from Dubai cancelled on Wednesday. Air India, operating 72 weekly flights from various Indian cities to Dubai, had to cancel flights due to adverse weather conditions in the Gulf nation. Other airlines, including Air India Express, Vistara, IndiGo, and SpiceJet, also saw disruptions in their Dubai-bound flights.
title: Air India, IndiGo cancel flights to Dubai amid airport flooding

description: New Zealand cricketer Ish Sodhi ventured into Punjabi commentary, showcasing his skills in a recent video shared by Pakistan Cricket. While recounting an encounter between Pakistan and New Zealand, Sodhi mistakenly referred to Babar Azam as "Babar Zaman," prompting laughter. The Pakistan-New Zealand T20 series, starting April 18 in Rawalpindi, serves as preparation for the T20 World Cup.
title: Watch - 'Yeh dekho Babar Zaman...': NZ star’s funny commentary

description: A Sydney bishop brutally stabbed during a live-streamed sermon said Thursday he is recovering and forgives his attacker, "You are my son." "I forgive whoever has done this act and I say to him: You are my son, I love you and I will always pray for you.
title: 'You are my son': Stabbed Sydney bishop forgives attacker

description: The nearest Indonesian international airport to a volcano that erupted five times in recent days has been ordered closed for 24 hours due to volcanic ash, the transport ministry said Thursday. Sam Ratulangi International Airport in the city of Manado, located more than 100 kilometres (62 miles) from Mount Ruang, was forced to close until Thursday evening "due to the spread of volcanic ash which could endanger flight safety," Ambar Suryoko, head of the Manado region airport authority office, said in a statement.
title: Indonesian volcano eruption forces evacuations

After careful consideration of customer reviews and researching things at our end, we have compiled here a list of some of the best 5 star ACs that you can buy online in India.
title: Best 5 star AC options: Check here

description: Rahul Narwekar, Maharashtra assembly speaker, expressed unwavering support for Geeta Gawli, backed by BJP in BMC polls, to become the Mumbai mayor. Narwekar's dedication to the ABS family, led by Arun Gawli, was emphasized.
title: Maha Speaker creates stir in BJP, says he’s part of Gawli party now

description: Unemployed Shakeel Sheikh arrested for attacking principal Bhagwat Gurav at Kharbao railway station over wife's service book issue. Gurav receiving treatment at Ayush Hospital, Kalyan. Case filed by Dombivli GRP.
title: Maharashtra man knifes principal over his wife not getting raise

description: Indian national Jaspal Singh, 57, tragically passed away at a hospital in Atlanta while awaiting deportation in the United States. The US Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) confirmed the incident, with an autopsy pending to determine the cause of death.
title: Indian national, 57, awaiting deportation dies in US hospital

description: In the early hours of Wednesday, a devastating accident on the Vakola flyover claimed the life of 34-year-old taxi driver Vivek Mishra and left three teenagers hospitalized. 19-year-old Samyak Raniwala, alongside two minors, crashed his speeding car into Mishra's taxi after losing control and flipping over the median. The group, returning from a late-night outing, faced the consequences of immense speed and loss of vehicle control. A criminal case for negligence and rash driving has been registered against Raniwala, as the police and eyewitnesses piece together the tragic events that unfolded between 3.35 am and 3.50 am.
title: Car 'speeding' on Mumbai flyover flips over, hits cab & kills its driver

description: Gujarat Titans captain Shubman Gill expressed disappointment after their poor batting performance against Delhi Capitals, resulting in the lowest total of the Indian Premier League 2024 season. The Gujarat-based team managed only 89 runs before being bowled out in 17.3 overs, while Delhi Capitals reached 90 in 8.4 overs with six wickets in hand.
title: 'Bad batting, poor shots': Gill on lowest IPL 2024 total

description: NCP MLC Eknath Khadse received four threatening calls, with the first from an international number on April 15, and three subsequent ones from domestic numbers on April 16. The caller claimed to be an aide of Dawood Ibrahim and Chhota Shakeel, speaking in Hindi and threatening Khadse's life if he didn't "mend his ways." Khadse, unable to discern the motive behind the calls, filed a complaint with the Muktainagar police in Jalgaon. The police, led by SP M C V Maheshwar Reddy, have registered a non-cognisable offence and are investigating the seriousness of the threat. Khadse, who had left BJP in 2016 and joined NCP in 2020, is planning to return to BJP.
title: Got 4 threat calls from ‘Dawood, Shakeel aide’: Eknath Khadse

description: This year the title has switched, with 12-time winner Singapore being edged out of the top spot by its Middle Eastern rival in the Skytrax World Airport Awards 2024. In a strong showing for Asia, Seoul Incheon bagged third place — also being named 2024’s most family friendly airport — while Tokyo’s twin facilities of Haneda and Narita took fourth and fifth spots.
title: Singapore no longer No.1; these are the world’s best airports of 2024

description: Tesla and Space X CEO Elon Musk's tweet from January has caught the attention of the US, possibly paving the way for India to get a permanent seat at the UNSC. Musk said in his tweet that it's 'crazy' that India doesn't have a permanent UNSC seat. He also said that powerful nations are hesitant to give up their power.
title: 'Need for reform': US on Musk's 'India permanent UNSC seat' tweet

description: Rohit Sharma will play his 250th IPL game against Punjab Kings after hitting an unbeaten 105 against Chennai Super Kings. MI won against Delhi Capitals and Royal Challengers Bengaluru. Suryakumar Yadav scored fifties against Punjab last edition. Mumbai and Punjab are both coming off losses in their last games and have each lost four games, thus pressure to perform will be intense on both teams.
title: Rohit set for big landmark as MI gear up for Punjab clash

description: AB de Villiers has praised Shivam Dube for his exceptional performance in the Indian Premier League season. De Villiers, known for his cricketing insights, praised Dube's contribution to CSK's success and noted that despite the high traffic, Dube has had a fantastic season and is a powerhouse heater. He believes Dube could potentially make the T20 World Cup squad.
title: 'The only problem is...': ABD on Shivam Dube's T20 WC chances

description: In Shakarpur, a 33-year-old MCA graduate murdered his wife and brother-in-law. The husband confessed to the crime after contradictions. Police investigate the case involving coaching online and the victim's teaching profession.
title: Man kills wife, her brother using screwdriver in Delhi

description: Dr Abdul Salam, BJP’s Muslim candidate, faces challenges in Malappuram. During an interaction with voters in a remote village near Pulikkal, he recounted his bitter experience after attending Eid Namaz at Madin Masjid in Malappuram town. Salam, a popular academic and former VC of Calicut University, faces challenges not just from his own community but also from his party’s disorganized machinery in Malappuram, he says.
title: In masjid & market, BJP’s Muslim candidate is treated as haram in Kerala

description: Delhi Police apprehended a group of bikers for allegedly engaging in reckless driving in the New Delhi area. The incident was brought to light by the patrolling staff of Parliament Street and Kartavya Path, who noticed the bikers driving in a dangerous manner at around 3:30 am.
title: Group of 28 bikers perform stunts on Delhi road, all arrested

description: Despite soaring gold prices, reaching $2,400 per ounce this year, devotees continue to generously donate gold to the Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams (TTD), the world's richest Hindu temple trust. In 2023, TTD recorded a deposit of 1,031 kg of gold valued at Rs 773 crore. The trust holds a total of 11,329 kg of gold, worth Rs 8,496 crore, in nationalised banks under the gold monetisation scheme. The trend of increasing gold donations persists even as the global economy faces uncertainty, with TTD receiving an average of one tonne of gold annually over the past four years. Alongside gold, TTD also receives substantial cash offerings, with an average monthly donation exceeding Rs 100 crore. The temple's hundi collection averages Rs 1,600 crore yearly. TTD's assets include Rs 19,000 crore in fixed deposits, nearly 14 tonnes of gold, and 85,000 acres of property, reinforcing its status as India's wealthiest temple trust.
title: Despite high prices, 1,031 kg gold donated to Tirumala trust in 2023

description: Prithviraj drove 2 km with a man hanging precariously on the footboard after a bike collision near Owaisi flyover. Sparks flew, passer-by's fate unknown, locals stopped the truck. Prithviraj faces charges for dangerous driving.
title: Man hangs on to truck racing away with bike under wheel for 2km

description: Tesla's board and Elon Musk are betting that shareholders will once again approve his ambitious compensation package from 2018, despite the electric vehicle market's evolution and the package's recent invalidation by a Delaware court. The board is relying on Musk's popularity and his role in Tesla's stock surge of approximately 700% over the past six years to persuade investors that he deserves the substantial compensation.
title: What Musk’s pay package vote means for his $174 bn fortune

description: Telangana gears up for Lok Sabha battle among Congress, BJP, and BRS. Nominations accepted April 18-25, polling on May 13. Congress aims to repeat 2023 assembly win, while BJP energized for electoral inroads.
title: Telangana set for battle royale as poll process begins

title: YouTuber arrested for claiming to be in KIA for one full day

title: Cast aside, Bengal’s Totos don’t care much about casting ballot

description: The impact of using impact subs in IPL 2024 raises concerns about its impact on the development of all-rounders in Indian cricket. Ravindra Jadeja shines as a rare example of a successful all-rounder amidst challenges faced by players like Hardik Pandya and Krunal Pandya. How Ajit Agarkar and company would love a few names as options for the allrounder's role as they go about picking the team for the T20 World Cup.
title: Impact player a hit for IPL, but is it good for Indian cricket?
